This paper is primarily focused on optimizing query processing in main memory database systems, which falls under the category of cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses the use of hash tables, which are a common data structure in computer science and could potentially fall under the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses optimization techniques and cost models, which could fall under the categories of cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
